Professor Chukwuma Charles Soludo was last Thursday sworn in as the fifth Governor of Anambra State. His wife, Nonye Chukwuma, is naturally the First Lady. 1. Nonye hails from lsuofia, Aguata LGA of Anambra State. 2. She was born on July 31, 1970. 3. She is 51 years old.   10 prominent siblings in sports     World Water Day: Six side effects of not drinking enough…     2022 WCQ: Seven things to know about Ndidi’s replacement,…   4. Nonye is believed to be a niece of the former Minister of Information Dora Akunyili. 5. She attended the University of Nigeria, Nsukka between 1991 and 1995 bagging a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science. 6. Nonye later proceeded to do her Master of Science in Accounting and Finance at the University of Westminster, UK in 2006 7. She is the founder and Chief Executive Officer of the food company, Healthy Living Foods Ltd, based in the UK. 8. She is also the Managing Director of a real estate company, Charles Frances Properties in London Family. 9. She has six children with Professor Charles Soludo.